1
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:04,565
<i>I've done it now...</i>

2
00:00:04,565 --> 00:00:07,365
<i>I've really done it now.</i>

3
00:00:07,365 --> 00:00:12,604
<i>Never thought I'd end up
doing that with Kazumi.</i>

4
00:00:14,432 --> 00:00:17,798
<i>I know I was drunk, but still...</i>

5
00:00:17,798 --> 00:00:19,778
Shut up.

6
00:00:21,501 --> 00:00:24,866
<i>With Kazumi of all people!</i>

7
00:00:30,414 --> 00:00:31,659
What's wrong?

8
00:00:31,659 --> 00:00:33,459
Huh?

9
00:00:35,159 --> 00:00:37,254
It's nothing.

10
00:00:45,931 --> 00:00:52,435
<i>I crossed the line with my best friend!</i>

11
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:54,972
Are you okay?

12
00:00:54,972 --> 00:00:56,815
Not feeling well?

13
00:00:57,984 --> 00:01:02,058
I think I might have a fever.

14
00:01:02,058 --> 00:01:03,920
I feel a little hot.

15
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:05,739
I need to use the restroom.

16
00:01:05,739 --> 00:01:07,206
Wait.

17
00:01:15,219 --> 00:01:19,692
<i>What was Kazumi thinking?</i>

18
00:01:19,692 --> 00:01:22,606
<i>Why did he say something like that?</i>

19
00:01:22,606 --> 00:01:28,213
I think compatibility is hard to know
until you give it a try.

20
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,433
Huh?

21
00:01:29,433 --> 00:01:34,363
Well then, let's end our friendship now.

22
00:01:34,363 --> 00:01:39,482
<i>He's never said that before, even as a joke.</i>

23
00:01:42,424 --> 00:01:48,658
I might not be able to look him in the eye.

24
00:02:42,708 --> 00:02:45,199
- Let's do it like that. Keep it up.
- Got it.

25
00:02:51,721 --> 00:02:54,925
That... was close...

26
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:57,206
Calm down, calm down.

27
00:02:57,206 --> 00:02:59,916
- Time for coffee.
- Shibasaki.

28
00:03:02,996 --> 00:03:04,525
Morning.

29
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:09,822
Good... morning.

30
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,609
You okay?

31
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,368
Yeah.

32
00:03:18,010 --> 00:03:20,391
Let's do our best today, too.

33
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:24,180
Let's do our best.

34
00:03:31,437 --> 00:03:32,734
- Hojo.
- Yeah?

35
00:03:32,734 --> 00:03:35,426
About the survey from the other day,

36
00:03:35,426 --> 00:03:38,510
how about using it at the next event?

37
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:41,103
Why does he seem so unbothered?

38
00:03:44,575 --> 00:03:48,553
<i>If you ask me what reaction I was expecting,</i>

39
00:03:48,553 --> 00:03:51,148
<i>honestly, I don't really know.</i>

40
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:52,865
<i>But...</i>

41
00:03:53,781 --> 00:03:56,653
<i>after feeling that good,</i>

42
00:03:56,653 --> 00:04:01,074
<i>things might get a bit complicated.</i>

43
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:06,337
<i>That's how perfectly aligned we were.</i>

44
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:14,428
<i>Unforgettably so...</i>

45
00:04:23,217 --> 00:04:25,507
Okay. Try revising it once more.

46
00:04:25,507 --> 00:04:27,024
Got it.

47
00:04:35,738 --> 00:04:38,111
Need him to see your draft?

48
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:40,697
Y-Yeah... yeah...

49
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:44,068
I'm done, so Hojo should be free now.

50
00:04:44,068 --> 00:04:46,043
Right.

51
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:54,010
Can you check my draft?

52
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:55,506
Okay.

53
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:58,564
Huh?

54
00:04:58,564 --> 00:05:00,433
Nothing...

55
00:05:04,978 --> 00:05:08,350
Okay, I'll get back to you as soon as I can.

56
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,693
Thank you.

57
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:15,148
<i>Either way, that was an accident!</i>

58
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,419
<i>Just an accident!</i>

59
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:22,155
<i>I'll avoid being alone
with Kazumi for a while.</i>

60
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:27,751
<i>Then eventually, we should be able
to go back to being just friends!</i>

61
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:45,720
Okay.

62
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:50,358
Then I'll share this information internally.

63
00:05:54,015 --> 00:05:55,794
Are you okay?

64
00:05:59,295 --> 00:06:00,655
Nihei.

65
00:06:00,655 --> 00:06:03,248
Did you revise yesterday's poster?

66
00:06:03,248 --> 00:06:04,658
Yes.

67
00:06:04,658 --> 00:06:07,993
I made two versions.

68
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:11,504
Option A is better.
The information is more organized.

69
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:19,428
<i>Can we really go back
to being friends like this?</i>

70
00:06:25,890 --> 00:06:28,908
Inviting us to eat out? This is rare.

71
00:06:28,908 --> 00:06:33,685
Well, sometimes I just want
to eat something nice outside.

72
00:06:33,685 --> 00:06:36,875
- Right! Let's go somewhere stylish!
- Yes, let's!

73
00:06:41,891 --> 00:06:43,922
Beef tongue stew sounds good.

74
00:06:43,922 --> 00:06:46,531
Sounds great. How about here?

75
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,599
- I'm in!
- I'll check if there are seats.

76
00:06:48,599 --> 00:06:50,436
Thanks.

77
00:06:53,081 --> 00:06:54,372
Shibasaki.

78
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:55,707
Yeah?

79
00:06:55,707 --> 00:06:58,635
Did something happen with Hojo?

80
00:06:59,307 --> 00:07:00,879
Why do you ask?

81
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:03,058
Not really.

82
00:07:03,058 --> 00:07:05,512
It just seemed like you were avoiding him.

83
00:07:05,512 --> 00:07:08,386
No, of course not.

84
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:11,727
Everything's normal. Same as always.

85
00:07:11,727 --> 00:07:13,646
Hey! Over here.

86
00:07:13,646 --> 00:07:15,359
What's up?

87
00:07:17,239 --> 00:07:20,020
- Come over here.
- What is it?

88
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:23,135
Look over there.

89
00:07:23,135 --> 00:07:24,802
It's Hojo.

90
00:07:24,802 --> 00:07:26,716
Huh?

91
00:07:26,716 --> 00:07:29,199
Huh? Okada?

92
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,388
Yeah.

93
00:07:30,388 --> 00:07:32,327
Okada's got game.

94
00:07:32,327 --> 00:07:34,960
The most popular girl in the company.

95
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,331
Is that so?

96
00:07:36,331 --> 00:07:38,806
With those looks and her personality,

97
00:07:38,806 --> 00:07:42,295
those defenseless old guys
have fallen hard for her.

98
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:46,635
Our company is basically
a sea of old corpses.

99
00:07:46,635 --> 00:07:48,385
That's terrifying.

100
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:50,470
Hojo is popular too, you know.

101
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,190
He's good at his job,

102
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:55,433
he looks after people,
and on top of that, he's handsome.

103
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,493
Huh...

104
00:07:57,493 --> 00:07:59,439
Hojo too?

105
00:07:59,439 --> 00:08:01,020
Yeah.

106
00:08:13,610 --> 00:08:21,761
<i>I've never minded seeing
Kazumi with other girls before.</i>

107
00:08:21,761 --> 00:08:23,423
<i>But...</i>

108
00:08:23,423 --> 00:08:27,634
<i>it looked like Kazumi and Okada
were getting along well.</i>

109
00:08:27,634 --> 00:08:31,928
<i>Maybe that's Kazumi's actual type.</i>

110
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:35,263
<i>Someone not as rough as me.</i>

111
00:08:35,263 --> 00:08:37,775
<i>Someone more feminine.</i>

112
00:08:40,322 --> 00:08:42,814
<i>This is definitely jealousy.</i>

113
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:47,475
<i>Even though I wanted
to go back to being friends...</i>

114
00:08:47,475 --> 00:08:51,372
What do I really want?

115
00:08:57,417 --> 00:08:59,907
[Vextos]

116
00:09:12,865 --> 00:09:14,854
Shibasaki.

117
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:18,558
Oh, sorry, did I startle you?

118
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:21,150
What is it?

119
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:23,615
I have something to carry
to the supply room.

120
00:09:23,615 --> 00:09:25,973
Could you help me?

121
00:09:25,973 --> 00:09:30,818
Well, sure, I can,
but wouldn't Nihei be better?

122
00:09:30,818 --> 00:09:32,935
Nihei's not around right now.

123
00:09:32,935 --> 00:09:35,207
Don't worry, it's not heavy.

124
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:37,744
Okay.

125
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,461
Sorry.

126
00:09:47,635 --> 00:09:49,346
Thanks.

127
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:53,751
Could you put these in by year?

128
00:09:53,751 --> 00:09:55,561
Got it.

129
00:10:15,574 --> 00:10:20,483
<i>Kazumi is acting the same as always.</i>

130
00:10:20,483 --> 00:10:23,693
<i>It's like I'm the only one
who's thinking about it.</i>

131
00:10:23,693 --> 00:10:25,549
<i>So frustrating.</i>

132
00:10:31,145 --> 00:10:33,807
Whoa! Are you okay?

133
00:10:34,433 --> 00:10:37,637
Still as clumsy as ever.

134
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:39,730
Did you sprain anything?

135
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:43,150
No, thanks.

136
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:48,072
You've been avoiding me lately, haven't you?

137
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:51,784
Is it because of what happened?

138
00:10:57,365 --> 00:11:00,960
Just focus on what feels good.

139
00:11:03,482 --> 00:11:08,459
Well, I was drunk, you know,
so I don't remember a thing.

140
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:10,639
Oh, is that so? Here's a rundown.

141
00:11:10,639 --> 00:11:13,759
No, that was a lie. I was lying.

142
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:18,227
So that wasn't enough for you, huh?

143
00:11:19,304 --> 00:11:23,394
I'll try harder so you're satisfied.

144
00:11:23,394 --> 00:11:24,851
You're too close.

145
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,527
Personal space!

146
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:30,345
Well, anyway, that's the last box, right?

147
00:11:30,345 --> 00:11:32,324
Then I'll be going.

148
00:11:35,379 --> 00:11:37,121
Don't run away.

149
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:42,000
I won't let things end like that.

150
00:11:47,231 --> 00:11:52,845
You're... a good listener.

151
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:55,750
I rely on you.

152
00:11:56,610 --> 00:11:58,767
And being with you is fun.

153
00:11:59,754 --> 00:12:01,770
But,

154
00:12:01,770 --> 00:12:04,577
if we go any further,

155
00:12:05,197 --> 00:12:10,279
I don't think
we can go back to being friends.

156
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:22,332
I'm scared of things changing.

157
00:12:29,094 --> 00:12:33,635
Do you really think
things can go back to how they were?

158
00:13:09,404 --> 00:13:13,300
If that's what you want,
should we go back...

159
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:17,429
to just being friends?

160
00:13:20,002 --> 00:13:22,474
Even if we do, I won't change.

161
00:13:23,557 --> 00:13:25,763
I won't leave you.

162
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:32,319
<i>I was the one scared of change...</i>

163
00:13:33,187 --> 00:13:37,533
<i>I was the one who pushed him away...</i>

164
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:41,218
<i>But if I could forget about the future,</i>

165
00:13:41,218 --> 00:13:43,372
<i>and just take the leap...</i>

166
00:13:45,586 --> 00:13:47,469
Kazumi,

167
00:13:48,596 --> 00:13:51,830
do you have someone you like?

168
00:13:53,181 --> 00:13:55,252
Yeah, I do.

169
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:57,628
I'm planning to properly confess soon.

170
00:13:57,628 --> 00:14:00,139
- So, Himari...
- I'll be going now.

171
00:14:09,402 --> 00:14:12,275
<i>So he does like someone.</i>

172
00:14:13,029 --> 00:14:17,614
<i>Is it Okada?</i>

173
00:14:21,196 --> 00:14:27,040
<i>What am I to Kazumi?</i>

174
00:14:28,314 --> 00:14:30,697
Jeez...

175
00:14:30,697 --> 00:14:34,256
If only the person he liked was me.

176
00:14:38,844 --> 00:14:43,265
[Welcome - Urban Vino Bal]
I'm the worst!

177
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:54,602
Not even being able
to support my best friend's love...

178
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:57,821
Am I really a good friend?

179
00:14:59,049 --> 00:15:01,471
I wonder what happened to Shibasaki.

180
00:15:01,471 --> 00:15:04,494
Well, I think I know the reason.

181
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:09,416
Come on, Shibasaki, cheer up.

182
00:15:13,048 --> 00:15:16,245
[Kazumi Hojo]

183
00:15:20,722 --> 00:15:24,389
Sorry for getting so down.

184
00:15:25,868 --> 00:15:27,748
Yeah, yeah.

185
00:15:29,409 --> 00:15:33,344
When this happens, drink it away!

186
00:15:33,344 --> 00:15:35,064
Right, right! Let's drink!

187
00:15:35,064 --> 00:15:36,489
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

188
00:15:36,489 --> 00:15:38,555
Cheers!

189
00:15:55,234 --> 00:15:57,277
No answer, huh...

190
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,503
Did I make her mad?

191
00:16:06,841 --> 00:16:08,484
We gave her too much to drink.

192
00:16:08,484 --> 00:16:10,510
You're the one who kept pushing her.

193
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:14,442
But what happened to her?

194
00:16:14,442 --> 00:16:17,192
You're so oblivious.

195
00:16:27,089 --> 00:16:28,176
[Kazumi Hojo]

196
00:16:28,176 --> 00:16:30,262
Hojo?

197
00:16:33,736 --> 00:16:36,503
This is an emergency.

198
00:16:38,944 --> 00:16:41,962
Hello, this is Ando.

199
00:16:41,962 --> 00:16:45,037
I actually want to ask you something.

200
00:16:45,037 --> 00:16:48,030
Yes. Of course.

201
00:17:02,589 --> 00:17:04,729
Over here, over here.

202
00:17:07,546 --> 00:17:09,272
Oh my...

203
00:17:09,272 --> 00:17:11,036
Well...

204
00:17:11,821 --> 00:17:15,777
It seems something sad happened.

205
00:17:16,668 --> 00:17:18,175
Oh, I see.

206
00:17:18,175 --> 00:17:19,660
Sorry for the trouble.

207
00:17:19,660 --> 00:17:20,915
Tell me about it!

208
00:17:20,915 --> 00:17:23,709
Anyway, Hojo, we'll leave the rest to you.

209
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:25,816
Please take Shibasaki home.

210
00:17:25,816 --> 00:17:26,887
Please.

211
00:17:26,887 --> 00:17:27,927
Please.

212
00:17:27,927 --> 00:17:31,037
Got it. Don't worry, I'll get her home.

213
00:17:31,037 --> 00:17:32,246
Thank you.

214
00:17:32,246 --> 00:17:34,186
Goodbye then.

215
00:17:53,956 --> 00:17:56,583
Himari, let's go.

216
00:17:59,346 --> 00:18:01,455
- Can you walk?
- Yeah.

217
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:04,011
The taxi's right over there. You can do it.

218
00:18:04,011 --> 00:18:05,543
Yeah.

219
00:18:05,543 --> 00:18:09,930
It's rare for you to drink
until you're that wasted.

220
00:18:12,340 --> 00:18:14,434
What were you talking about?

221
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:18,306
About you.

222
00:18:18,306 --> 00:18:19,856
Me?

223
00:18:20,993 --> 00:18:23,561
Kazumi, you idiot!

224
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:26,613
Was I just a game to you?

225
00:18:27,316 --> 00:18:29,194
Why do you think that?

226
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,948
I saw you having lunch with Okada.

227
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:37,700
That's what this is about?

228
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:40,317
What's that supposed to mean?

229
00:18:42,502 --> 00:18:44,589
Are you okay?

230
00:18:48,294 --> 00:18:52,021
That lunch stuff isn't what you think.

231
00:18:52,021 --> 00:18:54,850
We were just talking about work.

232
00:18:55,760 --> 00:19:00,633
If you do have someone you like,
I wish you'd told me.

233
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:02,843
That's...

234
00:19:04,429 --> 00:19:07,028
Sorry for confusing you.

235
00:19:13,573 --> 00:19:15,712
Kazumi.

236
00:19:17,111 --> 00:19:20,702
Are you this gentle with other people too?

237
00:19:23,651 --> 00:19:25,476
I'm not.

238
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:35,807
Himari?

239
00:20:20,683 --> 00:20:26,117
I only act this way with you, Himari.

240
00:20:29,012 --> 00:20:33,774
Kazumi, where is this?

241
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:35,700
My place.

242
00:20:36,444 --> 00:20:38,954
You wouldn't wake up.

243
00:20:40,710 --> 00:20:43,407
You can just stay over tonight.

244
00:20:45,189 --> 00:20:46,657
Okay.

245
00:20:58,895 --> 00:21:04,396
I can tell whether you're really
not okay with it.

246
00:21:06,069 --> 00:21:10,449
And I know everything you like.

247
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:34,847
I felt like I shouldn't touch you.

248
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:39,931
I felt like I didn't have the right.

249
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:44,044
But...

250
00:21:45,523 --> 00:21:48,231
you need me, Himari.

251
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:07,885
<i>This sensation isn't like the others.</i>

252
00:22:07,885 --> 00:22:10,086
<i>I want to believe in it.</i>

253
00:22:14,194 --> 00:22:18,356
<i>I know I won't be able to forget this.</i>

254
00:22:18,356 --> 00:22:22,443
<i>So much that it hurts.</i>

255
00:22:30,973 --> 00:22:34,117
<i>His gentle voice...</i>

256
00:22:34,117 --> 00:22:38,031
<i>The way he does things... All of it.</i>

257
00:22:39,645 --> 00:22:43,925
<i>I wish it was all just for me.</i>

258
00:22:48,579 --> 00:22:54,714
<i>I can't... just be a friend anymore.</i>

259
00:22:56,243 --> 00:22:59,161
<i>So, if that's true,</i>

260
00:22:59,161 --> 00:23:02,367
<i>I'd want us to stay like this forever, but...</i>

261
00:23:45,559 --> 00:23:49,236
Tonight, can I reserve you?

262
00:23:49,236 --> 00:23:51,482
Those two clearly like each other.

263
00:23:51,482 --> 00:23:52,907
Oh, wait.

264
00:23:52,907 --> 00:23:55,787
- You're cute, Shibasaki.
- Huh?

265
00:23:55,787 --> 00:23:58,826
<i>I need to tell her properly this time.</i>
